      • drop

        public boolean drop(Tile tile,
                    java.lang.String resource,
                    int amount)
        Drops some of the given resource on the beaver's Tile.
        Parameters:
        tile - The Tile to drop branches/food on. Must be the same Tile that the Beaver is on, or an adjacent one.
        resource - The type of resource to drop ('branches' or 'food').
        amount - The amount of the resource to drop, numbers <= 0 will drop all the resource type.
        Returns:
        True if successfully dropped the resource, false otherwise.

      • harvest

        Returns:
        True if successfully harvested, false otherwise.

      • pickup

        public boolean pickup(Tile tile,
                      java.lang.String resource,
                      int amount)
        Picks up some branches or food on the beaver's tile.
        Parameters:
        tile - The Tile to pickup branches/food from. Must be the same Tile that the Beaver is on, or an adjacent one.
        resource - The type of resource to pickup ('branches' or 'food').
        amount - The amount of the resource to drop, numbers <= 0 will pickup all of the resource type.
        Returns:
        True if successfully picked up a resource, false otherwise.
